This paper deals with unsupervised learning of probabilistic models, which is a central problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on designing models with tractable learning, sampling, inference, and evaluation. The paper proposes a new method using real-valued non-volume preserving (real NVP) transformations, which is a set of powerful invertible and learnable transformations. The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed method in modeling natural images on four datasets. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with information theory and neural networks, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories as well.
